'We have to negotiate in the end,' Kerry told CBS News. 'We've always
been willing to negotiate in the context of the Geneva I
process,' he added, referring to a 2012 conference which called
for a negotiated transition to end the conflict.

Kerry said the United States and other countries, which he
did not name, were exploring ways to reignite the diplomatic
process to end the conflict in Syria.

'What we're pushing for is to get him (Assad) to come and do
that, and it may require that there be increased pressure on him
of various kinds in order to do that,' the secretary of state
said.

